definitions.definition: ( nautical ) To propel a punt or similar craft by means of a pole.
Of a fish, to walk along the seafloor using its fins as limbs.

main_definition: ( nautical ) To propel a punt or similar craft by means of a pole.
secondary_definitions: Of a fish, to walk along the seafloor using its fins as limbs.

definitions.definition: To dropkick ; to kick something a considerable distance.

subdefinitions.definition: ( rugby , American football , Australian rules football , Gaelic football , soccer , transitive , intransitive ) To kick a ball dropped from the hands before it hits the ground. ( This puts the ball farther from the goal across which the opposing team is attempting to score, so improves the chances of the team punting. )
( soccer ) To kick a bouncing ball far and high.

definitions.definition: ( colloquial , intransitive ) To equivocate and delay or put off (answering a question, addressing an issue, etc).
To retreat from one's objective; to abandon an effort one still notionally supports.
( colloquial , intransitive ) To make the best choice from a set of non-ideal alternatives.
( colloquial , transitive ) To eject ; to kick out of a place.

main_definition: To dropkick ; to kick something a considerable distance.

( colloquial , transitive ) To eject ; to kick out of a place.

definitions.definition: To play at basset , baccara , faro , etc.
To stake against the bank, to back a horse, to gamble or take a chance more generally
To make a highly speculative investment or other commitment , or take a wild guess.

main_definition: To play at basset , baccara , faro , etc.
secondary_definitions: ( Australia , Ireland , New Zealand , UK ) To stake against the bank, to back a horse, to gamble or take a chance more generally
( figuratively ) To make a highly speculative investment or other commitment , or take a wild guess.
